458
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:27,786
AND THE REASON?

459
00:21:27,786 --> 00:21:30,873
I JUST REALLY WANT ONE.

460
00:21:30,873 --> 00:21:34,752
BUT YOU'RE NOT OLD ENOUGH
YET. I'D BE BREAKING THE LAW.

461
00:21:34,752 --> 00:21:37,254
BUT WE'RE ALREADY
NOTORIOUS TERRORISTS.

462
00:21:37,254 --> 00:21:39,757
NEVERTHELESS, I CAN'T
GIVE YOU A DRINK.

463
00:21:39,757 --> 00:21:41,300
BUT IT'S OKAY NOW.

464
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:43,302
HUH?

465
00:21:43,302 --> 00:21:45,679
ACCORDING TO
GREENWICH MEAN TIME...

466
00:21:45,679 --> 00:21:49,475
I JUST CAME OF AGE
A FEW MINUTES AGO...

467
00:21:49,475 --> 00:21:50,893
IS THAT SO...

468
00:21:50,893 --> 00:21:52,394
(Clink)

469
00:21:52,394 --> 00:21:54,563
THIS MIGHT SOUND STRANGE
UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES,

470
00:21:54,563 --> 00:21:56,065
BUT HERE'S TO YOU.

471
00:21:56,065 --> 00:21:59,026
THANKS FOR THE
BIRTHDAY WISH.

472
00:21:59,026 --> 00:22:01,612
(Gulping)

473
00:22:02,071 --> 00:22:04,323
WHY DRINK SOMETHING
SO BITTER?

474
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:05,574
(Chuckles)

475
00:22:05,574 --> 00:22:08,786
YOU'LL KNOW SOON ENOUGH,
I'M SURE OF IT.

476
